# QA Guidelines

## Local Development (Default)

For most local changes, **skip smoke tests**. Use fast checks only:

```bash
npm run check      # TypeScript typecheck (fast)
```

**Smoke tests (`npm run smoke`) are NOT required for every task.**

## When to Run Smoke Tests

Run smoke tests ONLY when:
1. User explicitly requests it ("run smoke", "full QA", "test everything")
2. Making significant changes to core CRM flows (products, orders, customers)
3. User says "done" or "ship it" on a major feature

## CI Automation

Smoke tests run automatically in GitHub Actions on:
- Push to main/develop branches
- Pull requests

## If Smoke Tests Are Requested

Run `npm run smoke` and report results:

```markdown
## QA Report

| Step | Result |
|------|--------|
| 1. Boot FE+BE | ✅/❌ |
| 2. Create Product | ✅/❌ |
| 3. List Products | ✅/❌ |
| 4. Edit Product | ✅/❌ |
| 5. Create Order | ✅/❌ |
| 6. Add Line Item | ✅/❌ |
| 7. Refresh | ✅/❌ |
| 8. No Errors | ✅/❌ |
```

## Skipping QA

For documentation-only changes or when user says "skip QA", state:
> "QA skipped - no code changes" or "QA skipped per user request"
